---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---
<Layout
  title="Tree Removal & Storm Response Cardinia Shire | Full Coverage | (03) 9003 0108"
  description="Tree removal, lopping, stump grinding & 24/7 storm response across all of Cardinia Shire — Pakenham, Officer, Beaconsfield, Cardinia Lakes, Heritage Springs and rural east. Cert IV arborists."
  canonical="https://cardiniatreeservices.com.au/cardinia-shire/">
  <section class="hero">
    <div class="hero-inner">
      <span class="hero-eyebrow">All of Cardinia Shire &middot; full coverage</span>
      <h1>Tree services across <span class="accent">Cardinia Shire</span>.</h1>
      <p class="hero-sub">
        From the Pakenham growth corridor in the west to Bunyip State Forest
        in the east, Beaconsfield in the south to the rural blocks up near
        Cardinia Reservoir. Cert IV arborists, AS 4373 pruning, $20M public
        liability, 24/7 storm response. Council planning mapping checked at
        every quote.
      </p>
      <div class="hero-actions">
        <a class="btn btn-primary" href="tel:+61390030108">&#9742; Call (03) 9003 0108</a>
        <a class="btn btn-ghost" href="/quote/">Get a fixed-price quote</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="section-inner">
      <span class="section-eyebrow">Full coverage</span>
      <h2>Suburbs we cover.</h2>
      <div class="divider"></div>
      <div style="max-width: 65rem;">
        <h3>Featured suburb pages.</h3>
        <p>Full local guides &mdash; what trees are common, what council mapping applies, what we typically do there.</p>
        <div class="areas-grid" style="margin: 1.5rem 0 2.5rem 0;">
          <a class="area-pill" href="/pakenham/">Pakenham</a>
          <a class="area-pill" href="/officer/">Officer</a>
          <a class="area-pill" href="/beaconsfield/">Beaconsfield</a>
          <a class="area-pill" href="/cardinia-lakes/">Cardinia Lakes</a>
          <a class="area-pill" href="/heritage-springs/">Heritage Springs</a>
        </div>

        <h3>Other Cardinia Shire suburbs we cover.</h3>
        <div class="areas-grid" style="margin: 1.5rem 0 2.5rem 0;">
          <span class="area-pill area-pill-static">Pakenham (CBD)</span>
          <span class="area-pill area-pill-static">Pakenham South</span>
          <span class="area-pill area-pill-static">Pakenham East</span>
          <span class="area-pill area-pill-static">Lakeside</span>
          <span class="area-pill area-pill-static">Beaconsfield Upper</span>
          <span class="area-pill area-pill-static">Toomuc Valley</span>
          <span class="area-pill area-pill-static">Nar Nar Goon</span>
          <span class="area-pill area-pill-static">Tynong</span>
          <span class="area-pill area-pill-static">Bunyip</span>
          <span class="area-pill area-pill-static">Garfield</span>
          <span class="area-pill area-pill-static">Maryknoll</span>
          <span class="area-pill area-pill-static">Tonimbuk</span>
          <span class="area-pill area-pill-static">Iona</span>
          <span class="area-pill area-pill-static">Cora Lynn</span>
          <span class="area-pill area-pill-static">Lang Lang</span>
          <span class="area-pill area-pill-static">Koo Wee Rup</span>
        </div>

        <h3 style="margin-top: 2rem;">Two zones, two arborist conversations.</h3>
        <p>
          <strong>Growth-corridor zone</strong> (Pakenham, Pakenham East,
          Lakeside, Cardinia Lakes, Heritage Springs, Officer Estate): newer
          estates built into ex-paddock land. Boundary gums on retained
          fence lines, building-pad clearing, post-build stump grinding,
          formative pruning of advanced ornamentals. Most blocks not inside
          a VPO. Standard storm response 60&ndash;90 minutes.
        </p>
        <p>
          <strong>Rural &amp; rural-residential zone</strong> (Beaconsfield
          Upper, Toomuc Valley, Bunyip, Garfield, Tynong, Tonimbuk, Maryknoll,
          Cora Lynn): 1&ndash;5+ acre blocks with mature native canopy &mdash;
          messmate, manna gum, swamp gum, narrow-leaf peppermint. VPO and ESO
          coverage common, BMO overlay across most. Removal, structural
          pruning, hazardous-tree assessment, defensible-space clearing under
          the 10/30 bushfire rule. Storm response 90&ndash;180 minutes.
        </p>

        <h3 style="margin-top: 2rem;">Council planning controls.</h3>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Significant Tree Register</strong> &mdash; named protected trees, planning permit required for any work. $9,000+ fines for unauthorised removal.</li>
          <li><strong>Vegetation Protection Overlay (VPO)</strong> &mdash; native trees over 10m height or 40cm diameter need planning permit. Common across older Pakenham, parts of Beaconsfield, Officer rural fringe, all of the eastern shire.</li>
          <li><strong>Environmental Significance Overlay (ESO)</strong> &mdash; biodiversity-protected areas. Common near Bunyip State Forest and Cardinia Reservoir margins.</li>
          <li><strong>Bushfire Management Overlay (BMO)</strong> &mdash; 10/30 vegetation-clearing rule allows defensible-space clearing without permit (10m from dwelling + modified vegetation 30m out). Most of the eastern and northern shire.</li>
          <li><strong>Heritage Overlay</strong> &mdash; restrictions on tree removal in heritage precincts (parts of older Pakenham, Officer, Garfield).</li>
        </ul>
        <p style="margin-top: 1rem;">
          We check the Cardinia Shire planning mapping for every quote and
          tell you exactly what&rsquo;s protected and what isn&rsquo;t.
          Where a permit is needed we lodge it on your behalf.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section section-alt">
    <div class="section-inner">
      <span class="section-eyebrow">All five services</span>
      <h2>What we do.</h2>
      <div class="svc-grid">
        <a class="svc-card" href="/services/tree-removal/"><h3>Tree removal</h3><p>$800&ndash;$15,000. Climbed, sectional, EWP or crane access.</p><span class="svc-link">See &rarr;</span></a>
        <a class="svc-card" href="/services/tree-lopping/"><h3>Lopping &amp; pruning</h3><p>$300&ndash;$1,500. AS 4373 cuts. Crown reduction, deadwooding, formative.</p><span class="svc-link">See &rarr;</span></a>
        <a class="svc-card" href="/services/stump-grinding/"><h3>Stump grinding</h3><p>$150&ndash;$500. Below-grade for paving/planting. Narrow-access grinder.</p><span class="svc-link">See &rarr;</span></a>
        <a class="svc-card" href="/services/storm-response/"><h3>Storm response</h3><p>$400&ndash;$1,800+. 24/7. Insurance docs included. 60&ndash;180 min response.</p><span class="svc-link">See &rarr;</span></a>
        <a class="svc-card" href="/services/land-clearing/"><h3>Land clearing</h3><p>$2K&ndash;$8K/acre. Building-pad, subdivision, paddock revival.</p><span class="svc-link">See &rarr;</span></a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="section-inner">
      <div class="cta-block">
        <h2>Free quote anywhere in Cardinia Shire.</h2>
        <p>Growth corridor or rural east. Planning check at the quote stage. Fixed-price written quote within 2&ndash;5 working days.</p>
        <div class="hero-actions" style="justify-content:center;">
          <a class="btn btn-primary" href="tel:+61390030108">&#9742; Call (03) 9003 0108</a>
          <a class="btn btn-ghost" href="/quote/">Book online</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
